@node "wasmacht" "What does DirText?"

 Dir Text reads your ASCII files and converts every line to a file in a chosen
 directory.

 This looks very cool and is great, but simple effect.

@endnode

@node "System" "Requirements"

 Dir Text requires at least OS2.0 and reqtools.library from Nico Françios.
 
 A faster processor and fast ram would be very useful.

@endnode

@node "Copyright" "Copyright"

 Dir Text is copyrighted by me, Andreas Falkenhahn. All rights reserved. This
 prog is cardware. If you use it, it would be nice if you send me a postcard
 from your hometown.

 reqtools.library is © by Niço François

@endnode

@node "cardware" "How to use"

 Simply doubleclick on the icon to start and hear the great sound (thanx to
 placid/vision and 4-mat). 

 First click on about and see some infos.

 Now click on create it. You`ll now asked, where to create the files. Select
 a dir and click on OK.

 Now you`ll be asked to select an ASCII file. Select the one you`ve edited 
 with an normal ASCII editor like GoldED or MegaED. 

 Now the conversion will begin. If all went succesfull you`ll hear another
 nice peace of sound.


 ERRORS:

 The most existing error is the wrong chars requester. That means, that aa
 few chars can`t be used as filenames, here are two: "/:\"
 The prog will show you which char has activated the error. So you can fix
 it.

 So, thats all folks! Use it & have fun, but don`t forget to send me a post- 
 card.

@endnode

